(Decision
    "Introspection observes both public-layer operations AND Sema-effect-layer operations. persona-introspect consumes all contract crates so it knows about every observable type. The mechanism: a universal observer hook on every daemon — whenever a message arrives or a Sema effect happens, the daemon checks for a subscribed observer lane and sends a copy if present. Subscribing to that hook is done on the daemon's normal (public) socket, not the owner socket — observation isn't a security concern because no secrets cross the wire, and putting it on the owner socket would create ambiguity about which owner observation belongs to. The interface is a debug surface for the engine."
    "I think introspection should be able to introspect anything. … both the semi effect and the public layer observation. So persona introspect still consumes all the contracts. … there could be maybe a universal kind of hook. Whenever a message arrives, it looks for an observer lane. And just sends a copy there, if it's there. … Subscribing to these events would be done on the public socket. Or the, yeah, the normal socket."
